{"type":"message","id":"fa1dce0b","parentId":"89aede8a","timestamp":"2026-03-04T05:13:30.409Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"看起来这个工具在QVeris上有问题。让我试试EODHD的新闻API，它成功率更高(0.987)。","thinkingSignature":"7db94b66f6fc7db2fb0e07c9e39335880b138e057ca4f138d010f002d5312f3d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4c2dfd1ue36z_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace && node scripts/qveris_tool.mjs execute \"eodhd.news.retrieve.v1.fe8bf94c\" --params '{\"t\": \"technology\", \"limit\": 20}' 2>&1","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":11352,"output":109,"cacheRead":13984,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":25445,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772601205836}}
{"type":"message","id":"98496940","parentId":"fa1dce0b","timestamp":"2026-03-04T05:13:39.179Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_4c2dfd1ue36z_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"execution_id\": \"4c151699-3e79-4688-9dca-2cda36d8d92d\",\n  \"result\": {\n    \"status_code\": 200,\n    \"message\": \"Result content is too long (283202 bytes). You can reference the truncated content (20480 bytes) and download the full content from the url provided.\",\n    \"full_content_file_url\": \"http://qveris-tool-results-cache-bj.oss-cn-beijing.aliyuncs.com/tool_result_cache%2F20260304%2Feodhd.news.retrieve.v1.fe8bf94c%2F06557009bd49458980f7feead378b09e.json?OSSAccessKeyId=LTAI5tM3qNRZSgSrg1iSTALm&Expires=1772608418&Signature=Qq2hQ6HdiVP2QXulmIrIDU6CW7c%3D\",\n    \"truncated_content\": \"[{\\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-04T05:00:00+00:00\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"D.R. Horton's Southwest Florida Division Announces Driftwood Bay, a New Home Community in Port Charlotte, Florida\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"PORT CHARLOTTE, FLORIDA / ACCESS Newswire / March 4, 2026 / D.R. Horton's Southwest Florida Division, is excited to introduce Driftwood Bay, a thoughtfully designed new home community in Port Charlotte. Driftwood Bay brings attainable homeownership and D.R. Horton's quality construction, modern floorplans and exceptional Southwest Florida lifestyle to one of the region's fastest-growing coastal areas in Port Charlotte.\\\\n\\\\nDriftwood Bay features a collection of single-family homes designed for today's homebuyers, with open-concept layouts, energy-efficient features, and upgraded finishes. Homes range from just over 1,300 square feet to over 1,600 square feet, and include spacious kitchens with stainless steel appliances, smart home technology packages, and flexible living spaces ideal for individuals, families and seasonal residents alike.\\\\n\\\\nConveniently located near shopping, dining, golf courses, boating, and Gulf Coast beaches, Driftwood Bay provides residents with easy access to everything that makes Charlotte County a desirable place to live. The community's location also offers proximity to major roadways such as: Veterans Blvd, Tamiami Trail (US-41), I-75 (Located at exit 170), and Kings Highway connecting to I-75, making commuting to nearby employment, shopping, and schools seamless.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\\\\"As demand continues to grow in Southwest Florida, Driftwood Bay delivers the quality, value, and lifestyle buyers expect from D.R. Horton\\\\\\\" said Dwayne Hill, Division President of D.R. Horton Southwest Florida Division. \\\\\\\"We are excited to offer homebuyers an opportunity to enjoy new construction at a tremendous value, all while living in the heart of Port Charlotte.\\\\\\\"\\\\n\\\\nHomes at Driftwood Bay are currently competitively priced in the mid-$200's, making them an attractive option for first-time homebuyers, families, move-up homebuyers, and those relocating to Florida.\\\\n\\\\nFor more information about Driftwood Bay in Port Charlotte, please visit https://www.drhorton.com/florida/southwest-florida/port-charlotte/driftwood-bay or contact our online sales concierge team to schedule a tour by calling 239-413-9776.\\\\n\\\\nAbout D.R. Horton\\\\n\\\\nD.R. Horton, \\\\\\\"America's Builder,\\\\\\\" has been building families beautiful homes in desirable locations for 47 years. America's largest homebuilder by volume since 2002, D.R. Horton has built more than 1,200,000 homes with quality, functionality, value and style in mind. For more information about D.R. Horton's Southwest Florida division, please call (239) 225-2636 or visit www.drhorton.com/florida/southwest-florida. Home and community information, including pricing, included features, terms, availability and amenities, are subject to change at any time without notice or obligation. Homes subject to prior sale. Prices do not include closing costs or other fees that are payable by the homebuyer. Square footage dimensions are approximate. A D.R. Horton Smart Home is equipped with technology that includes some or all of the following Internet-connected devices: a video doorbell, a programmable thermostat; a door lock; a smart light switch; a touchscreen smart home control device, a garage door opener and a smart speaker, all of which are integrated by an automation platform hosted by Alarm.com. D.R. Horton reserves the right, without prior notice, to substitute other products for those listed above. Other Smart Home technology features may be offered for an additional charge. For Smart Home technology included in the home to work, homeowners must obtain and pay for their own Internet service and may need to purchase compatible devices and to maintain accounts with third parties for the services. D.R. Horton makes no representation or warranty that any or all of the Smart Home technology is secure, will meet any homeowner needs or will provide any level of physical or cyber security for the home - even if the technology is working as intended. See a D.R. Horton representative for complete information. Appliances include washer, dryer, refrigerator, dishwasher, microwave and stovetop/oven combination. Appliance make and model may vary due to supply availability. See sales agent for complete appliance details. D.R. Horton is an equal housing opportunity builder. © 2026. D.R. Horton, Inc. All rights reserved. Revised 3/2/2026.\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\nMedia Contact:\\\\r\\\\nZach Bouchard\\\\r\\\\nSouthwest Florida Marketing Manager\\\\r\\\\nD.R. Horton\\\\r\\\\n(239) 225-2636\\\\r\\\\nzjbouchard@drhorton.com\\\\n\\\\nStory Continues\\\\n\\\\nSOURCE: D.R. Horton Southwest Florida Division\\\\n\\\\nRelated Documents:\\\\n\\\\n01 05\\\\n\\\\nView the original press release on ACCESS Newswire\\\\n\\\\nView Comments\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://finance.yahoo.com/news/d-r-hortons-southwest-florida-050000929.html\\\", \\\"symbols\\\": [\\\"DHI.US\\\", \\\"HO2.DU\\\", \\\"HO2.MU\\\"], \\\"tags\\\": [\\\"HOMEBUILDERS\\\", \\\"REAL-ESTATE\\\"], \\\"sentiment\\\": {\\\"polarity\\\": 0.997, \\\"neg\\\": 0.007, \\\"neu\\\": 0.872, \\\"pos\\\": 0.121}}, {\\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-04T04:42:42+00:00\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Cryoport outlines $190M–$194M 2026 revenue target as commercial cell therapy drives growth\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"Earnings Call Insights: Cryoport, Inc. (CYRX) Q4 2025\\\\n\\\\nMANAGEMENT VIEW\\\\n\\\\n \\\\t* CEO Jerrell Shelton reported \\\\\\\"full year revenue from continuing operations of $176.2 million, exceeding the high end of our prior guidance and reflecting continued momentum across our core markets.\\\\\\\" Shelton highlighted double-digit revenue growth in Q4, with commercial cell and gene therapy revenue increasing 29% year-over-year to $33.4 million for 2025, and clinical trial revenue up 14% to $47.1 million. \\\\n \\\\t* Shelton noted that Cryoport supported a record 760 clinical trials and 20 commercial therapies worldwide by year-end, representing \\\\\\\"approximately 70% of total trials for the cell and gene therapy industry.\\\\\\\"\\\\n \\\\t* Shelton stated, \\\\\\\"For 2025, revenue from our Life Sciences Services segment increased 18% year-over-year, including 22% growth in BioStorage/BioServices revenue.\\\\\\\"\\\\n \\\\t* Management emphasized new product launches, including MVE's integrated condition monitoring solutions and the Fusion 800 Series self-sustaining cryogenic freezer, which \\\\\\\"opens up substantial market opportunities.\\\\\\\"\\\\n \\\\t* Strategic investments were made in the company's Global Supply Chain Centers in Paris and California, along with a partnership with DHL and new collaborations with Cardinal Health and Parexel.\\\\n \\\\t* CFO Robert Stefanovich stated, \\\\\\\"Our cost reduction initiatives contributed to our gross margin of 47%, accompanied by a $12 million year-over-year improvement in adjusted EBITDA. With our progress to date, we anticipate achieving positive adjusted EBITDA in the second half of 2026.\\\\\\\"\\\\n\\\\nOUTLOOK\\\\n\\\\n \\\\t* The company issued full year 2026 revenue guidance of $190 million to $194 million, with Shelton describing this range as \\\\\\\"an appropriate starting point for the year.\\\\\\\"\\\\n \\\\t* Stefanovich confirmed, \\\\\\\"We anticipate achieving positive adjusted EBITDA in the second half of 2026.\\\\\\\"\\\\n \\\\t* Management expects continued growth in all service and product lines, with commercial cell therapy identified as the primary driver.\\\\n\\\\nFINANCIAL RESULTS\\\\n\\\\n \\\\t* Fourth quarter revenue growth was supported by commercial cell and gene therapy activity and \\\\\\\"revenue from the support of commercial cell and gene therapy increasing 29% year-over-year to a record $33.4 million for the year.\\\\\\\"\\\\n \\\\t* Clinical trial revenue was reported at $47.1 million, up 14% year-over-year.\\\\n \\\\t* The Life Sciences Services segment delivered 18% growth, and BioStorage/BioServices revenue increased 22%.\\\\n \\\\t* MVE Biological Solutions' revenue grew 7% year-over-year, while cost reduction initiatives resulted in a gross margin of 47%.\\\\n\\\\nQ&A\\\\n\\\\n \\\\t* Puneet Souda, Leerink Partners LLC: Asked about guidance, segment growth, and commercial therapy momentum. Shelton reiterated confidence in commercial therapy as a future driver and noted expectations for \\\\\\\"another good year in '26,\\\\\\\" while Sawicki confirmed commercial revenue now exceeds 20% of total revenue.\\\\n \\\\t* Souda also inquired about geopolitical flight disruptions and Q1 visibility. Shelton replied, \\\\\\\"There's nothing that we're expecting in terms of cancellations. And today, there's been minimal impact on us.\\\\\\\"\\\\n \\\\t* Anna Snopkowski, KeyBanc: Asked about the lag between funding and customer activity. Sawicki explained, \\\\\\\"You'll typically see that kick in after about a half a year time frame.\\\\\\\"\\\\n \\\\t* Snopkowski requested margin improvement drivers. Stefanovich stated, \\\\\\\"It's really less about cost reduction milestones,\\\\\\\" citing investments in supply chain centers and expected growth and efficiencies.\\\\n \\\\t* Subhalaxmi Nambi, Guggenheim: Asked about macro environment assumptions. Stefanovich highlighted progress in clinical trials and felt \\\\\\\"quite comfortable with the guidance that we're providing.\\\\\\\"\\\\n \\\\t* David Saxon, Needham: Queried about MVE growth outlook—Sawicki and Shelton signaled mid- to high-single-digit growth, with innovation continuing.\\\\n \\\\t* Steven Etoch, Stephens: Asked about FDA's single pivotal trial policy impact. Sawicki said, \\\\\\\"If they follow through with a single pivotal and don't require a follow-up, that's beneficial to us.\\\\\\\"\\\\n \\\\t* David Larsen, BTIG: Asked about MVE product revenue growth. Shelton advised focusing on annual growth due to the nature of capital equipment sales. Sawicki described demand as stabilizing across product portfolios and regions.\\\\n\\\\nSENTIMENT ANALYSIS\\\\n\\\\n \\\\t* Analysts pressed for segment-level clarity and the impact of new regulatory and funding environments, maintaining a neutral to slightly positive tone, as seen in Snopkowski's congratulatory remarks and targeted follow-ups on margin drivers.\\\\n \\\\t* Management maintained a confident and constructive tone, emphasizing momentum, strategic execution, and operational discipline. Phrases such as \\\\\\\"I'm certain about that\\\\\\\" and \\\\\\\"we're forecasting 9 new therapies in 2026\\\\\\\" demonstrated conviction, while Stefanovich acknowledged macro uncertainty yet expressed comfort with guidance.\\\\n \\\\t* Compared to the previous quarter, both analysts and management continued to show cautious optimism, with management expressing increased confidence in commercial therapy growth and adjusted EBITDA targets.\\\\n\\\\nQUARTER-OVER-QUARTER COMPARISON\\\\n\\\\n \\\\t* Current quarter guidance increased to a $190 million–$194 million range for 2026, up from the previous full-year 2025 guidance of $170 million–$174 million.\\\\n \\\\t* Commercial cell and gene therapy revenue growth moderated from 36% in Q3 to 29% for the full year, while the number of clinical trials supported rose from 745 to 760.\\\\n \\\\t* Management's tone remained confident, but with heightened emphasis on strategic partnerships, product innovation, and the path to profitability. Analysts continued to focus on segment performance and macro risks, with recurring questions on margin improvement and growth drivers.\\\\n \\\\t* The push for positive adjusted EBITDA shifted from \\\\\\\"as early as year-end\\\\\\\" in Q3 to \\\\\\\"second half of 2026.\\\\\\\"\\\\n\\\\nRISKS AND CONCERNS\\\\n\\\\n \\\\t* Macro volatility and regulatory agency challenges were acknowledged by Stefanovich, but no specific risks were identified as impacting the 2026 outlook.\\\\n \\\\t* Management cited the need to remain \\\\\\\"opportunistic\\\\\\\" in growth investments and noted that new product launches and partnerships may take time to fully impact results.\\\\n \\\\t* Analysts raised concerns about potential geopolitical disruptions and the pace of benefits from strategic partnerships like DHL, but management reported minimal current impact.\\\\n\\\\nFINAL TAKEAWAY\\\\n\\\\nCryoport closed 2025 with revenue from continuing operations surpassing guidance, driven by record growth in commercial cell and gene therapy and expanding service offerings. Management projects further growth in 2026, with revenue guidance set at $190 million–$194 million and a target for positive adjusted EBITDA in the second half of the year. Strategic partnerships, new product innovations, and a robust clinical trial pipeline position the company for continued leadership in temperature-controlled supply chain solutions for the cell and gene therapy industry.\\\\n\\\\nRead the full Earnings Call Transcript [https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/cyrx/earnings/transcripts]\\\\n\\\\nMORE ON CRYOPORT\\\\n\\\\n \\\\t* Cryoport, Inc. (CYRX) Q4 2025 Earnings Call Transcript [https://seekingalpha.com/article/4878070-cryoport-inc-cyrx-q4-2025-earnings-call-transcript]\\\\n \\\\t* Cryoport, Inc. 2025 Q4 - Results - Earnings Call Presentation [https://seekingalpha.com/article/4877930-cryoport-inc-2025-q4-results-earnings-call-presentation]\\\\n \\\\t* Seeking Alpha’s Quant Rating on CryoPort [https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CYRX/ratings/quant-ratings]\\\\n \\\\t* Historical earnings data for CryoPort [https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CYRX/earnings]\\\\n \\\\t* Financial information for CryoPort [https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CYRX/income-statement]\\\\n\\\\n \\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4560516-cryoport-outlines-190m-194m-2026-revenue-target-as-commercial-cell-therapy-drives-growth?utm_source=feed_news_all&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;feed_item_type=news\\\", \\\"symbols\\\": [\\\"CYRX.US\\\"], \\\"tags\\\": [\\\"BIOTECH\\\", \\\"CELL-THERAPY\\\", \\\"EARNINGS\\\", \\\"GUIDANCE\\\", \\\"RATINGS\\\", \\\"REVENUE GROWTH\\\", \\\"SUPPLY-CHAIN\\\", \\\"TOTAL REVENUE\\\"], \\\"sentiment\\\": {\\\"polarity\\\": 0.998, \\\"neg\\\": 0.025, \\\"neu\\\": 0.855, \\\"pos\\\": 0.12}}, {\\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-04T04:37:15+00:00\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Is Occidental Petroleum (OXY) Pricing Fair After Its Strong Year To Date Rally?\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"Track your investments for FREE with Simply Wall St, the portfolio command center trusted by over 7 million individual investors worldwide.\\\\n\\\\nIf you are wondering whether Occidental Petroleum is offering good value right now, the key is to look past the headlines and focus on what the current price actually reflects. The stock last closed at US$53.68, with returns of 3.3% over 7 days, 18.3% over 30 days, 26.7% year to date, 17.9% over 1 year, and a 3 year return of negative 7.3% alongside a 5 year return of 98.8%. Recent news coverage around Occidental Petroleum has often focused on its role as a large US oil and gas producer and its exposure to energy market sentiment, which helps frame how investors are reacting to shifts in the sector. Broader discussions about capital allocation, balance sheet priorities, and long term energy trends also give context to why the share price has moved the way it has. According to Simply Wall St's framework, Occidental Petroleum currently has a valuation score of 2 out of 6. This means it screens as undervalued on two of six checks and sets up a closer look at different valuation methods, before finishing with an even more practical way to think about the stock's value at the end of this article.\\\\n\\\\nOccidental Petroleum scores just 2/6 on our valuation checks. See what other red flags we found in the full valuation breakdown.\\\\n\\\\nApproach 1: Occidental Petroleum Discounted Cash Flow (DCF) Analysis\\\\n\\\\nA Discounted Cash Flow model takes estimates of the cash a business may generate in the future, then discounts those cash flows back to today to arrive at an estimated intrinsic value per share.\\\\n\\\\nFor Occidental Petroleum, the latest twelve month Free Cash Flow is about $4.38b. Using a 2 Stage Free Cash Flow to Equity model, analysts provide explicit forecasts through 2030, with Simply Wall St extending those projections further based on those inputs. For example, projected Free Cash Flow for 2030 is $4.35b, with intermediate years in the $3.56b to $4.41b range once you look at the annual figures in the model.\\\\n\\\\nAfter discounting this stream of projected cash flows to today, the DCF model arrives at an estimated intrinsic value of $103.93 per share, compared with the recent share price of $53.68. On this basis, the stock screens as about 48.4% undervalued.\\\\n\\\\nResult: UNDERVALUED\\\\n\\\\nOur Discounted Cash Flow (DCF) analysis suggests Occidental Petroleum is undervalued by 48.4%. Track this in your watchlist or portfolio, or discover 49 more high quality undervalued stocks.OXY Discounted Cash Flow as at Mar 2026\\\\n\\\\nHead to the Valuation section of our Company Report for more details on how we arrive at this Fair Value for Occidental Petroleum.\\\\n\\\\nStory Continues\\\\n\\\\nApproach 2: Occidental Petroleum Price vs Earnings\\\\n\\\\nFor profitable companies, the P/E ratio is a useful way to connect what you are paying for each share with the earnings the business is currently generating. It gives you a quick sense of how many dollars investors are willing to pay today for one dollar of current earnings.\\\\n\\\\nWhat counts as a “normal” P/E depends on how investors see the company’s growth prospects and risk. Higher expected growth or lower perceived risk can support a higher P/E, while lower growth expectations or higher risk usually go with a lower P/E.\\\\n\\\\nOccidental Petroleum currently trades on a P/E of 39.22x. That is above the Oil and Gas industry average of 14.36x and also above the peer group average of 27.21x. Simply Wall St’s “Fair Ratio” for Occidental Petroleum is 27.15x. This Fair Ratio is a proprietary estimate of what the P/E might reasonably be, given factors such as earnings growth, industry, profit margin, market cap and company specific risks.\\\\n\\\\nThe Fair Ratio can be more informative than a simple peer or industry comparison because it adjusts for these company specific traits. Comparing 39.22x to the Fair Ratio of 27.15x suggests the shares are pricing in more optimistic conditions than this framework implies.\\\\n\\\\nResult: OVERVALUEDNYSE:OXY P/E Ratio as at Mar 2026\\\\n\\\\nP/E ratios tell one story, but what if the real opportunity lies elsewhere? Start investing in legacies, not executives. Discover our 18 top founder-led companies.\\\\n\\\\nUpgrade Your Decision Making: Choose your Occidental Petroleum Narrative\\\\n\\\\nEarlier we mentioned that there is an even better way to understand valuation, so let us introduce you to Narratives, a simple way for you to spell out your story for Occidental Petroleum, link that story to your own revenue, earnings and margin assumptions, and then see the Fair Value that drops out of those numbers.\\\\n\\\\nOn Simply Wall St’s Community page, Narratives let you turn your view of the business into a transparent forecast that you can compare directly to today’s price. This can help you decide whether you see a gap between what you think the shares are worth and where they are trading.\\\\n\\\\nBecause Narratives update automatically when new information such as news or earnings is added to the platform, you are not locked into a static view and can quickly see how fresh data shifts your Fair Value versus the current price.\\\\n\\\\nFor Occidental Petroleum, one investor Narrative currently points to a Fair Value of US$16.62 per share while another points to US$68.29. This shows how two people can look at the same company, plug in very different revenue growth, profit margin and discount rate assumptions, and end up with very different conclusions about whether the stock looks expensive or cheap to them.\\\\n\\\\nFor Occidental Petroleum, here are previews of two leading Occidental Petroleum narratives:\\\\n\\\\n🐂 Occidental Petroleum Bull Case\\\\n\\\\nFair Value: US$55.05\\\\n\\\\nRecent Price vs Fair Value: about 2.5% below this narrative fair value based on the last close of US$53.68\\\\n\\\\nRevenue Growth Assumption: 4%\\\\n\\\\nViews Occidental as building a dual engine over time, with core Permian oil and gas plus a growing carbon capture and storage business that could add a new revenue stream if it scales. Assumes ongoing focus on debt reduction, operational efficiency and contributions from chemicals and midstream to support free cash flow. Notes that if carbon capture becomes commercially meaningful, future valuation multiples could reflect both traditional energy and carbon management earnings.\\\\n\\\\n🐻 Occidental Petroleum Bear Case\\\\n\\\\nFair Value: US$48.94\\\\n\\\\nRecent Price vs Fair Value: about 9.7% above this narrative fair value based on the last close of US$53.68\\\\n\\\\nRevenue Growth Assumption: 7.47% decline\\\\n\\\\nDescribes cash flows as tied closely to oil demand, with exposure to commodity cycles, sector shifts, higher leverage after acquisitions and potential strain from capital intensive carbon projects. Highlights risks around oil price volatility, possible pressure on OxyChem margins from global oversupply, labor and technology execution challenge\",\n    \"content_schema\": {\n      \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/schema#\",\n      \"type\": \"array\",\n      \"items\": {\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"properties\": {\n          \"date\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\"\n          },\n          \"title\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\"\n          },\n          \"content\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\"\n          },\n          \"link\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\"\n          },\n          \"symbols\": {\n            \"type\": \"array\",\n            \"items\": {\n              \"type\": \"string\"\n            }\n          },\n          \"tags\": {\n            \"type\": \"array\",\n            \"items\": {\n              \"type\": \"string\"\n            }\n          },\n          \"sentiment\": {\n            \"anyOf\": [\n              {\n                \"type\": \"null\"\n              },\n              {\n                \"type\": \"object\",\n                \"properties\": {\n                  \"polarity\": {\n                    \"type\": \"number\"\n                  },\n                  \"neg\": {\n                    \"type\": \"number\"\n                  },\n                  \"neu\": {\n                    \"type\": \"number\"\n                  },\n                  \"pos\": {\n                    \"type\": \"number\"\n                  }\n                },\n                \"required\": [\n                  \"neg\",\n                  \"neu\",\n                  \"polarity\",\n                  \"pos\"\n                ]\n              }\n            ]\n          }\n        },\n        \"required\": [\n          \"content\",\n          \"date\",\n          \"link\",\n          \"sentiment\",\n          \"symbols\",\n          \"tags\",\n          \"title\"\n        ]\n      }\n    }\n  },\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"elapsed_time_ms\": 1814.24,\n  \"cost\": 6.5\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":8765,"aggregated":"{\n  \"execution_id\": \"4c151699-3e79-4688-9dca-2cda36d8d92d\",\n  \"result\": {\n    \"status_code\": 200,\n    \"message\": \"Result content is too long (283202 bytes). You can reference the truncated content (20480 bytes) and download the full content from the url provided.\",\n    \"full_content_file_url\": \"http://qveris-tool-results-cache-bj.oss-cn-beijing.aliyuncs.com/tool_result_cache%2F20260304%2Feodhd.news.retrieve.v1.fe8bf94c%2F06557009bd49458980f7feead378b09e.json?OSSAccessKeyId=LTAI5tM3qNRZSgSrg1iSTALm&Expires=1772608418&Signature=Qq2hQ6HdiVP2QXulmIrIDU6CW7c%3D\",\n    \"truncated_content\": \"[{\\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-04T05:00:00+00:00\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"D.R. Horton's Southwest Florida Division Announces Driftwood Bay, a New Home Community in Port Charlotte, Florida\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"PORT CHARLOTTE, FLORIDA / ACCESS Newswire / March 4, 2026 / D.R. Horton's Southwest Florida Division, is excited to introduce Driftwood Bay, a thoughtfully designed new home community in Port Charlotte. Driftwood Bay brings attainable homeownership and D.R. Horton's quality construction, modern floorplans and exceptional Southwest Florida lifestyle to one of the region's fastest-growing coastal areas in Port Charlotte.\\\\n\\\\nDriftwood Bay features a collection of single-family homes designed for today's homebuyers, with open-concept layouts, energy-efficient features, and upgraded finishes. Homes range from just over 1,300 square feet to over 1,600 square feet, and include spacious kitchens with stainless steel appliances, smart home technology packages, and flexible living spaces ideal for individuals, families and seasonal residents alike.\\\\n\\\\nConveniently located near shopping, dining, golf courses, boating, and Gulf Coast beaches, Driftwood Bay provides residents with easy access to everything that makes Charlotte County a desirable place to live. The community's location also offers proximity to major roadways such as: Veterans Blvd, Tamiami Trail (US-41), I-75 (Located at exit 170), and Kings Highway connecting to I-75, making commuting to nearby employment, shopping, and schools seamless.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\\\\"As demand continues to grow in Southwest Florida, Driftwood Bay delivers the quality, value, and lifestyle buyers expect from D.R. Horton\\\\\\\" said Dwayne Hill, Division President of D.R. Horton Southwest Florida Division. \\\\\\\"We are excited to offer homebuyers an opportunity to enjoy new construction at a tremendous value, all while living in the heart of Port Charlotte.\\\\\\\"\\\\n\\\\nHomes at Driftwood Bay are currently competitively priced in the mid-$200's, making them an attractive option for first-time homebuyers, families, move-up homebuyers, and those relocating to Florida.\\\\n\\\\nFor more information about Driftwood Bay in Port Charlotte, please visit https://www.drhorton.com/florida/southwest-florida/port-charlotte/driftwood-bay or contact our online sales concierge team to schedule a tour by calling 239-413-9776.\\\\n\\\\nAbout D.R. Horton\\\\n\\\\nD.R. Horton, \\\\\\\"America's Builder,\\\\\\\" has been building families beautiful homes in desirable locations for 47 years. America's largest homebuilder by volume since 2002, D.R. Horton has built more than 1,200,000 homes with quality, functionality, value and style in mind. For more information about D.R. Horton's Southwest Florida division, please call (239) 225-2636 or visit www.drhorton.com/florida/southwest-florida. Home and community information, including pricing, included features, terms, availability and amenities, are subject to change at any time without notice or obligation. Homes subject to prior sale. Prices do not include closing costs or other fees that are payable by the homebuyer. Square footage dimensions are approximate. A D.R. Horton Smart Home is equipped with technology that includes some or all of the following Internet-connected devices: a video doorbell, a programmable thermostat; a door lock; a smart light switch; a touchscreen smart home control device, a garage door opener and a smart speaker, all of which are integrated by an automation platform hosted by Alarm.com. D.R. Horton reserves the right, without prior notice, to substitute other products for those listed above. Other Smart Home technology features may be offered for an additional charge. For Smart Home technology included in the home to work, homeowners must obtain and pay for their own Internet service and may need to purchase compatible devices and to maintain accounts with third parties for the services. D.R. Horton makes no representation or warranty that any or all of the Smart Home technology is secure, will meet any homeowner needs or will provide any level of physical or cyber security for the home - even if the technology is working as intended. See a D.R. Horton representative for complete information. Appliances include washer, dryer, refrigerator, dishwasher, microwave and stovetop/oven combination. Appliance make and model may vary due to supply availability. See sales agent for complete appliance details. D.R. Horton is an equal housing opportunity builder. © 2026. D.R. Horton, Inc. All rights reserved. Revised 3/2/2026.\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\nMedia Contact:\\\\r\\\\nZach Bouchard\\\\r\\\\nSouthwest Florida Marketing Manager\\\\r\\\\nD.R. Horton\\\\r\\\\n(239) 225-2636\\\\r\\\\nzjbouchard@drhorton.com\\\\n\\\\nStory Continues\\\\n\\\\nSOURCE: D.R. Horton Southwest Florida Division\\\\n\\\\nRelated Documents:\\\\n\\\\n01 05\\\\n\\\\nView the original press release on ACCESS Newswire\\\\n\\\\nView Comments\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://finance.yahoo.com/news/d-r-hortons-southwest-florida-050000929.html\\\", \\\"symbols\\\": [\\\"DHI.US\\\", \\\"HO2.DU\\\", \\\"HO2.MU\\\"], \\\"tags\\\": [\\\"HOMEBUILDERS\\\", \\\"REAL-ESTATE\\\"], \\\"sentiment\\\": {\\\"polarity\\\": 0.997, \\\"neg\\\": 0.007, \\\"neu\\\": 0.872, \\\"pos\\\": 0.121}}, {\\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-04T04:42:42+00:00\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Cryoport outlines $190M–$194M 2026 revenue target as commercial cell therapy drives growth\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"Earnings Call Insights: Cryoport, Inc. (CYRX) Q4 2025\\\\n\\\\nMANAGEMENT VIEW\\\\n\\\\n \\\\t* CEO Jerrell Shelton reported \\\\\\\"full year revenue from continuing operations of $176.2 million, exceeding the high end of our prior guidance and reflecting continued momentum across our core markets.\\\\\\\" Shelton highlighted double-digit revenue growth in Q4, with commercial cell and gene therapy revenue increasing 29% year-over-year to $33.4 million for 2025, and clinical trial revenue up 14% to $47.1 million. \\\\n \\\\t* Shelton noted that Cryoport supported a record 760 clinical trials and 20 commercial therapies worldwide by year-end, representing \\\\\\\"approximately 70% of total trials for the cell and gene therapy industry.\\\\\\\"\\\\n \\\\t* Shelton stated, \\\\\\\"For 2025, revenue from our Life Sciences Services segment increased 18% year-over-year, including 22% growth in BioStorage/BioServices revenue.\\\\\\\"\\\\n \\\\t* Management emphasized new product launches, including MVE's integrated condition monitoring solutions and the Fusion 800 Series self-sustaining cryogenic freezer, which \\\\\\\"opens up substantial market opportunities.\\\\\\\"\\\\n \\\\t* Strategic investments were made in the company's Global Supply Chain Centers in Paris and California, along with a partnership with DHL and new collaborations with Cardinal Health and Parexel.\\\\n \\\\t* CFO Robert Stefanovich stated, \\\\\\\"Our cost reduction initiatives contributed to our gross margin of 47%, accompanied by a $12 million year-over-year improvement in adjusted EBITDA. With our progress to date, we anticipate achieving positive adjusted EBITDA in the second half of 2026.\\\\\\\"\\\\n\\\\nOUTLOOK\\\\n\\\\n \\\\t* The company issued full year 2026 revenue guidance of $190 million to $194 million, with Shelton describing this range as \\\\\\\"an appropriate starting point for the year.\\\\\\\"\\\\n \\\\t* Stefanovich confirmed, \\\\\\\"We anticipate achieving positive adjusted EBITDA in the second half of 2026.\\\\\\\"\\\\n \\\\t* Management expects continued growth in all service and product lines, with commercial cell therapy identified as the primary driver.\\\\n\\\\nFINANCIAL RESULTS\\\\n\\\\n \\\\t* Fourth quarter revenue growth was supported by commercial cell and gene therapy activity and \\\\\\\"revenue from the support of commercial cell and gene therapy increasing 29% year-over-year to a record $33.4 million for the year.\\\\\\\"\\\\n \\\\t* Clinical trial revenue was reported at $47.1 million, up 14% year-over-year.\\\\n \\\\t* The Life Sciences Services segment delivered 18% growth, and BioStorage/BioServices revenue increased 22%.\\\\n \\\\t* MVE Biological Solutions' revenue grew 7% year-over-year, while cost reduction initiatives resulted in a gross margin of 47%.\\\\n\\\\nQ&A\\\\n\\\\n \\\\t* Puneet Souda, Leerink Partners LLC: Asked about guidance, segment growth, and commercial therapy momentum. Shelton reiterated confidence in commercial therapy as a future driver and noted expectations for \\\\\\\"another good year in '26,\\\\\\\" while Sawicki confirmed commercial revenue now exceeds 20% of total revenue.\\\\n \\\\t* Souda also inquired about geopolitical flight disruptions and Q1 visibility. Shelton replied, \\\\\\\"There's nothing that we're expecting in terms of cancellations. And today, there's been minimal impact on us.\\\\\\\"\\\\n \\\\t* Anna Snopkowski, KeyBanc: Asked about the lag between funding and customer activity. Sawicki explained, \\\\\\\"You'll typically see that kick in after about a half a year time frame.\\\\\\\"\\\\n \\\\t* Snopkowski requested margin improvement drivers. Stefanovich stated, \\\\\\\"It's really less about cost reduction milestones,\\\\\\\" citing investments in supply chain centers and expected growth and efficiencies.\\\\n \\\\t* Subhalaxmi Nambi, Guggenheim: Asked about macro environment assumptions. Stefanovich highlighted progress in clinical trials and felt \\\\\\\"quite comfortable with the guidance that we're providing.\\\\\\\"\\\\n \\\\t* David Saxon, Needham: Queried about MVE growth outlook—Sawicki and Shelton signaled mid- to high-single-digit growth, with innovation continuing.\\\\n \\\\t* Steven Etoch, Stephens: Asked about FDA's single pivotal trial policy impact. Sawicki said, \\\\\\\"If they follow through with a single pivotal and don't require a follow-up, that's beneficial to us.\\\\\\\"\\\\n \\\\t* David Larsen, BTIG: Asked about MVE product revenue growth. Shelton advised focusing on annual growth due to the nature of capital equipment sales. Sawicki described demand as stabilizing across product portfolios and regions.\\\\n\\\\nSENTIMENT ANALYSIS\\\\n\\\\n \\\\t* Analysts pressed for segment-level clarity and the impact of new regulatory and funding environments, maintaining a neutral to slightly positive tone, as seen in Snopkowski's congratulatory remarks and targeted follow-ups on margin drivers.\\\\n \\\\t* Management maintained a confident and constructive tone, emphasizing momentum, strategic execution, and operational discipline. Phrases such as \\\\\\\"I'm certain about that\\\\\\\" and \\\\\\\"we're forecasting 9 new therapies in 2026\\\\\\\" demonstrated conviction, while Stefanovich acknowledged macro uncertainty yet expressed comfort with guidance.\\\\n \\\\t* Compared to the previous quarter, both analysts and management continued to show cautious optimism, with management expressing increased confidence in commercial therapy growth and adjusted EBITDA targets.\\\\n\\\\nQUARTER-OVER-QUARTER COMPARISON\\\\n\\\\n \\\\t* Current quarter guidance increased to a $190 million–$194 million range for 2026, up from the previous full-year 2025 guidance of $170 million–$174 million.\\\\n \\\\t* Commercial cell and gene therapy revenue growth moderated from 36% in Q3 to 29% for the full year, while the number of clinical trials supported rose from 745 to 760.\\\\n \\\\t* Management's tone remained confident, but with heightened emphasis on strategic partnerships, product innovation, and the path to profitability. Analysts continued to focus on segment performance and macro risks, with recurring questions on margin improvement and growth drivers.\\\\n \\\\t* The push for positive adjusted EBITDA shifted from \\\\\\\"as early as year-end\\\\\\\" in Q3 to \\\\\\\"second half of 2026.\\\\\\\"\\\\n\\\\nRISKS AND CONCERNS\\\\n\\\\n \\\\t* Macro volatility and regulatory agency challenges were acknowledged by Stefanovich, but no specific risks were identified as impacting the 2026 outlook.\\\\n \\\\t* Management cited the need to remain \\\\\\\"opportunistic\\\\\\\" in growth investments and noted that new product launches and partnerships may take time to fully impact results.\\\\n \\\\t* Analysts raised concerns about potential geopolitical disruptions and the pace of benefits from strategic partnerships like DHL, but management reported minimal current impact.\\\\n\\\\nFINAL TAKEAWAY\\\\n\\\\nCryoport closed 2025 with revenue from continuing operations surpassing guidance, driven by record growth in commercial cell and gene therapy and expanding service offerings. Management projects further growth in 2026, with revenue guidance set at $190 million–$194 million and a target for positive adjusted EBITDA in the second half of the year. Strategic partnerships, new product innovations, and a robust clinical trial pipeline position the company for continued leadership in temperature-controlled supply chain solutions for the cell and gene therapy industry.\\\\n\\\\nRead the full Earnings Call Transcript [https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/cyrx/earnings/transcripts]\\\\n\\\\nMORE ON CRYOPORT\\\\n\\\\n \\\\t* Cryoport, Inc. (CYRX) Q4 2025 Earnings Call Transcript [https://seekingalpha.com/article/4878070-cryoport-inc-cyrx-q4-2025-earnings-call-transcript]\\\\n \\\\t* Cryoport, Inc. 2025 Q4 - Results - Earnings Call Presentation [https://seekingalpha.com/article/4877930-cryoport-inc-2025-q4-results-earnings-call-presentation]\\\\n \\\\t* Seeking Alpha’s Quant Rating on CryoPort [https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CYRX/ratings/quant-ratings]\\\\n \\\\t* Historical earnings data for CryoPort [https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CYRX/earnings]\\\\n \\\\t* Financial information for CryoPort [https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CYRX/income-statement]\\\\n\\\\n \\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4560516-cryoport-outlines-190m-194m-2026-revenue-target-as-commercial-cell-therapy-drives-growth?utm_source=feed_news_all&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;feed_item_type=news\\\", \\\"symbols\\\": [\\\"CYRX.US\\\"], \\\"tags\\\": [\\\"BIOTECH\\\", \\\"CELL-THERAPY\\\", \\\"EARNINGS\\\", \\\"GUIDANCE\\\", \\\"RATINGS\\\", \\\"REVENUE GROWTH\\\", \\\"SUPPLY-CHAIN\\\", \\\"TOTAL REVENUE\\\"], \\\"sentiment\\\": {\\\"polarity\\\": 0.998, \\\"neg\\\": 0.025, \\\"neu\\\": 0.855, \\\"pos\\\": 0.12}}, {\\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-04T04:37:15+00:00\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Is Occidental Petroleum (OXY) Pricing Fair After Its Strong Year To Date Rally?\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"Track your investments for FREE with Simply Wall St, the portfolio command center trusted by over 7 million individual investors worldwide.\\\\n\\\\nIf you are wondering whether Occidental Petroleum is offering good value right now, the key is to look past the headlines and focus on what the current price actually reflects. The stock last closed at US$53.68, with returns of 3.3% over 7 days, 18.3% over 30 days, 26.7% year to date, 17.9% over 1 year, and a 3 year return of negative 7.3% alongside a 5 year return of 98.8%. Recent news coverage around Occidental Petroleum has often focused on its role as a large US oil and gas producer and its exposure to energy market sentiment, which helps frame how investors are reacting to shifts in the sector. Broader discussions about capital allocation, balance sheet priorities, and long term energy trends also give context to why the share price has moved the way it has. According to Simply Wall St's framework, Occidental Petroleum currently has a valuation score of 2 out of 6. This means it screens as undervalued on two of six checks and sets up a closer look at different valuation methods, before finishing with an even more practical way to think about the stock's value at the end of this article.\\\\n\\\\nOccidental Petroleum scores just 2/6 on our valuation checks. See what other red flags we found in the full valuation breakdown.\\\\n\\\\nApproach 1: Occidental Petroleum Discounted Cash Flow (DCF) Analysis\\\\n\\\\nA Discounted Cash Flow model takes estimates of the cash a business may generate in the future, then discounts those cash flows back to today to arrive at an estimated intrinsic value per share.\\\\n\\\\nFor Occidental Petroleum, the latest twelve month Free Cash Flow is about $4.38b. Using a 2 Stage Free Cash Flow to Equity model, analysts provide explicit forecasts through 2030, with Simply Wall St extending those projections further based on those inputs. For example, projected Free Cash Flow for 2030 is $4.35b, with intermediate years in the $3.56b to $4.41b range once you look at the annual figures in the model.\\\\n\\\\nAfter discounting this stream of projected cash flows to today, the DCF model arrives at an estimated intrinsic value of $103.93 per share, compared with the recent share price of $53.68. On this basis, the stock screens as about 48.4% undervalued.\\\\n\\\\nResult: UNDERVALUED\\\\n\\\\nOur Discounted Cash Flow (DCF) analysis suggests Occidental Petroleum is undervalued by 48.4%. Track this in your watchlist or portfolio, or discover 49 more high quality undervalued stocks.OXY Discounted Cash Flow as at Mar 2026\\\\n\\\\nHead to the Valuation section of our Company Report for more details on how we arrive at this Fair Value for Occidental Petroleum.\\\\n\\\\nStory Continues\\\\n\\\\nApproach 2: Occidental Petroleum Price vs Earnings\\\\n\\\\nFor profitable companies, the P/E ratio is a useful way to connect what you are paying for each share with the earnings the business is currently generating. It gives you a quick sense of how many dollars investors are willing to pay today for one dollar of current earnings.\\\\n\\\\nWhat counts as a “normal” P/E depends on how investors see the company’s growth prospects and risk. Higher expected growth or lower perceived risk can support a higher P/E, while lower growth expectations or higher risk usually go with a lower P/E.\\\\n\\\\nOccidental Petroleum currently trades on a P/E of 39.22x. That is above the Oil and Gas industry average of 14.36x and also above the peer group average of 27.21x. Simply Wall St’s “Fair Ratio” for Occidental Petroleum is 27.15x. This Fair Ratio is a proprietary estimate of what the P/E might reasonably be, given factors such as earnings growth, industry, profit margin, market cap and company specific risks.\\\\n\\\\nThe Fair Ratio can be more informative than a simple peer or industry comparison because it adjusts for these company specific traits. Comparing 39.22x to the Fair Ratio of 27.15x suggests the shares are pricing in more optimistic conditions than this framework implies.\\\\n\\\\nResult: OVERVALUEDNYSE:OXY P/E Ratio as at Mar 2026\\\\n\\\\nP/E ratios tell one story, but what if the real opportunity lies elsewhere? Start investing in legacies, not executives. Discover our 18 top founder-led companies.\\\\n\\\\nUpgrade Your Decision Making: Choose your Occidental Petroleum Narrative\\\\n\\\\nEarlier we mentioned that there is an even better way to understand valuation, so let us introduce you to Narratives, a simple way for you to spell out your story for Occidental Petroleum, link that story to your own revenue, earnings and margin assumptions, and then see the Fair Value that drops out of those numbers.\\\\n\\\\nOn Simply Wall St’s Community page, Narratives let you turn your view of the business into a transparent forecast that you can compare directly to today’s price. This can help you decide whether you see a gap between what you think the shares are worth and where they are trading.\\\\n\\\\nBecause Narratives update automatically when new information such as news or earnings is added to the platform, you are not locked into a static view and can quickly see how fresh data shifts your Fair Value versus the current price.\\\\n\\\\nFor Occidental Petroleum, one investor Narrative currently points to a Fair Value of US$16.62 per share while another points to US$68.29. This shows how two people can look at the same company, plug in very different revenue growth, profit margin and discount rate assumptions, and end up with very different conclusions about whether the stock looks expensive or cheap to them.\\\\n\\\\nFor Occidental Petroleum, here are previews of two leading Occidental Petroleum narratives:\\\\n\\\\n🐂 Occidental Petroleum Bull Case\\\\n\\\\nFair Value: US$55.05\\\\n\\\\nRecent Price vs Fair Value: about 2.5% below this narrative fair value based on the last close of US$53.68\\\\n\\\\nRevenue Growth Assumption: 4%\\\\n\\\\nViews Occidental as building a dual engine over time, with core Permian oil and gas plus a growing carbon capture and storage business that could add a new revenue stream if it scales. Assumes ongoing focus on debt reduction, operational efficiency and contributions from chemicals and midstream to support free cash flow. Notes that if carbon capture becomes commercially meaningful, future valuation multiples could reflect both traditional energy and carbon management earnings.\\\\n\\\\n🐻 Occidental Petroleum Bear Case\\\\n\\\\nFair Value: US$48.94\\\\n\\\\nRecent Price vs Fair Value: about 9.7% above this narrative fair value based on the last close of US$53.68\\\\n\\\\nRevenue Growth Assumption: 7.47% decline\\\\n\\\\nDescribes cash flows as tied closely to oil demand, with exposure to commodity cycles, sector shifts, higher leverage after acquisitions and potential strain from capital intensive carbon projects. Highlights risks around oil price volatility, possible pressure on OxyChem margins from global oversupply, labor and technology execution challenge\",\n    \"content_schema\": {\n      \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/schema#\",\n      \"type\": \"array\",\n      \"items\": {\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"properties\": {\n          \"date\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\"\n          },\n          \"title\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\"\n          },\n          \"content\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\"\n          },\n          \"link\": {\n            \"type\": \"string\"\n          },\n          \"symbols\": {\n            \"type\": \"array\",\n            \"items\": {\n              \"type\": \"string\"\n            }\n          },\n          \"tags\": {\n            \"type\": \"array\",\n            \"items\": {\n              \"type\": \"string\"\n            }\n          },\n          \"sentiment\": {\n            \"anyOf\": [\n              {\n                \"type\": \"null\"\n              },\n              {\n                \"type\": \"object\",\n                \"properties\": {\n                  \"polarity\": {\n                    \"type\": \"number\"\n                  },\n                  \"neg\": {\n                    \"type\": \"number\"\n                  },\n                  \"neu\": {\n                    \"type\": \"number\"\n                  },\n                  \"pos\": {\n                    \"type\": \"number\"\n                  }\n                },\n                \"required\": [\n                  \"neg\",\n                  \"neu\",\n                  \"polarity\",\n                  \"pos\"\n                ]\n              }\n            ]\n          }\n        },\n        \"required\": [\n          \"content\",\n          \"date\",\n          \"link\",\n          \"sentiment\",\n          \"symbols\",\n          \"tags\",\n          \"title\"\n        ]\n      }\n    }\n  },\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"elapsed_time_ms\": 1814.24,\n  \"cost\": 6.5\n}","cwd":"/Users/lynch/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772601219177}}
